11/07/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Croatia has been providing advice to Serbia on how to persuade the EU that it is co-operating fully with the UN tribunal, international media reported on Monday (10 July).
The two countries, which fought a bloody war 11 years ago, are now working together to help each other on the road to EU membership.
According to media reports, Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica has been seeking recommendations from his Croatian counterpart, Ivo Sanader.
(Guardian, The New York Times - 11/07/06;
AP, AFP, Reuters, UPI - 10/07/06)
